---
You are building a premium B2B wholesale catalog for District Flowers, a high-end flower importer based in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.

DESIGN PHILOSOPHY:
- Editorial luxury aesthetic — think Wallpaper* magazine meets wholesale trade
- Every pixel must feel intentional. No generic AI-generated UI.
- Whitespace is used generously. Density only where it serves function.
- Typography carries the design — Playfair Display for product names, DM Mono for all data, labels, prices, and UI chrome

BRAND TOKENS (never deviate from these):
- Background primary: #fbfbf8
- Background secondary: #f4f3ee
- Brand green: #20322a
- Lavender accent: #816aa0
- Rose accent: #E85A6B
- Border default: rgba(32,50,42,0.15)
- Border emphasis: rgba(32,50,42,0.35)

TYPOGRAPHY RULES:
- Flower names: Playfair Display, 18-20px, weight 700, color #20322a
- Product subtitle: DM Mono, 11px, weight 400, letter-spacing 0.08em, color rgba(32,50,42,0.55), ALL CAPS
- Column headers: DM Mono, 9px, weight 400, letter-spacing 0.15em, ALL CAPS, color rgba(32,50,42,0.5)
- Prices: DM Mono, 16px, weight 500, color #20322a
- UI labels: DM Mono, 10-11px, letter-spacing 0.1em, ALL CAPS

COMPONENT RULES:
- Buttons: 2-4px border-radius max. Flat. Never rounded pill shapes.
- Inputs: 1px border, no border-radius. Clean rectangular.
- Rows: no drop shadows. Borders only. Alternating background.
- Country badges: 32px circle, 2-letter ISO code, 1px border, country name beside it
- Stock: YES in muted green, NO with strikethrough in muted color
- Price format: always "SAR X.XX"

LAYOUT RULES:
- Max content width: 900px centered
- Row height: minimum 100px
- Column grid: 90px | 1fr | 140px | 80px | 130px
- Sticky: filter bar only
- Spacing: multiples of 8px

INTERACTION:
- Row hover: background shifts to #eae9e2
- Filter changes: 200ms stagger fade-in on rows
- Active filters: filled green background #20322a, cream text #fbfbf8

CODE QUALITY:
- TypeScript with proper interfaces, no any types
- Tailwind for layout, CSS variables for brand colors
- Separate reusable components: ProductRow, OriginBadge, StockIndicator, PriceDisplay
- All Supabase calls go through /lib/supabase.ts only
- API routes validate all inputs and return proper HTTP error codes
---
